10605 u32 exec_control, vmcs12_exec_ctrl;
10606
10607 vmcs_write16(GUEST_ES_SELECTOR, vmcs12->guest_es_selector);
10608 vmcs_write16(GUEST_CS_SELECTOR, vmcs12->guest_cs_selector);
10609 vmcs_write16(GUEST_SS_SELECTOR, vmcs12->guest_ss_selector);
10610 vmcs_write16(GUEST_DS_SELECTOR, vmcs12->guest_ds_selector);
10611 vmcs_write16(GUEST_FS_SELECTOR, vmcs12->guest_fs_selector);
10612 vmcs_write16(GUEST_GS_SELECTOR, vmcs12->guest_gs_selector);
10613 vmcs_write16(GUEST_LDTR_SELECTOR, vmcs12->guest_ldtr_selector);
10614 vmcs_write16(GUEST_TR_SELECTOR, vmcs12->guest_tr_selector);
10615 vmcs_write32(GUEST_ES_LIMIT, vmcs12->guest_es_limit);
10616 vmcs_write32(GUEST_CS_LIMIT, vmcs12->guest_cs_limit);
10617 vmcs_write32(GUEST_SS_LIMIT, vmcs12->guest_ss_limit);
10618 vmcs_write32(GUEST_DS_LIMIT, vmcs12->guest_ds_limit);
10619 vmcs_write32(GUEST_FS_LIMIT, vmcs12->guest_fs_limit);
10620 vmcs_write32(GUEST_GS_LIMIT, vmcs12->guest_gs_limit);
10621 vmcs_write32(GUEST_LDTR_LIMIT, vmcs12->guest_ldtr_limit);
10622 vmcs_write32(GUEST_TR_LIMIT, vmcs12->guest_tr_limit);
10623 vmcs_write32(GUEST_GDTR_LIMIT, vmcs12->guest_gdtr_limit);
10624 vmcs_write32(GUEST_IDTR_LIMIT, vmcs12->guest_idtr_limit);
10625 vmcs_write32(GUEST_ES_AR_BYTES, vmcs12->guest_es_ar_bytes);
10626 vmcs_write32(GUEST_CS_AR_BYTES, vmcs12->guest_cs_ar_bytes);
10627 vmcs_write32(GUEST_SS_AR_BYTES, vmcs12->guest_ss_ar_bytes);
10628 vmcs_write32(GUEST_DS_AR_BYTES, vmcs12->guest_ds_ar_bytes);
10629 vmcs_write32(GUEST_FS_AR_BYTES, vmcs12->guest_fs_ar_bytes);
10630 vmcs_write32(GUEST_GS_AR_BYTES, vmcs12->guest_gs_ar_bytes);
10631 vmcs_write32(GUEST_LDTR_AR_BYTES, vmcs12->guest_ldtr_ar_bytes);
10632 vmcs_write32(GUEST_TR_AR_BYTES, vmcs12->guest_tr_ar_bytes);
10633 vmcs_writel(GUEST_ES_BASE, vmcs12->guest_es_base);
10634 vmcs_writel(GUEST_CS_BASE, vmcs12->guest_cs_base);
10635 vmcs_writel(GUEST_SS_BASE, vmcs12->guest_ss_base);
10636 vmcs_writel(GUEST_DS_BASE, vmcs12->guest_ds_base);
10637 vmcs_writel(GUEST_FS_BASE, vmcs12->guest_fs_base);
10638 vmcs_writel(GUEST_GS_BASE, vmcs12->guest_gs_base);
10639 vmcs_writel(GUEST_LDTR_BASE, vmcs12->guest_ldtr_base);
10640 vmcs_writel(GUEST_TR_BASE, vmcs12->guest_tr_base);
10641 vmcs_writel(GUEST_GDTR_BASE, vmcs12->guest_gdtr_base);
10642 vmcs_writel(GUEST_IDTR_BASE, vmcs12->guest_idtr_base);
10643
10644 if (from_vmentry &&
10645 (vmcs12->vm_entry_controls & VM_ENTRY_LOAD_DEBUG_CONTROLS)) {
10646 kvm_set_dr(vcpu, 7, vmcs12->guest_dr7);
10647 vmcs_write64(GUEST_IA32_DEBUGCTL, vmcs12->guest_ia32_debugctl);
10648 } else {
10649 kvm_set_dr(vcpu, 7, vcpu->arch.dr7);
10650 vmcs_write64(GUEST_IA32_DEBUGCTL, vmx->nested.vmcs01_debugctl);
10651 }
10652 if (from_vmentry) {
10653 vmcs_write32(VM_ENTRY_INTR_INFO_FIELD,
10654 vmcs12->vm_entry_intr_info_field);
10655 vmcs_write32(VM_ENTRY_EXCEPTION_ERROR_CODE,
10656 vmcs12->vm_entry_exception_error_code);
10657 vmcs_write32(VM_ENTRY_INSTRUCTION_LEN,
10658 vmcs12->vm_entry_instruction_len);
10659 vmcs_write32(GUEST_INTERRUPTIBILITY_INFO,
10660 vmcs12->guest_interruptibility_info);
10661 vmx->loaded_vmcs->nmi_known_unmasked =
10662 !(vmcs12->guest_interruptibility_info & GUEST_INTR_STATE_NMI);
10663 } else {
10664 vmcs_write32(VM_ENTRY_INTR_INFO_FIELD, 0);
10665 }
10666 vmcs_write32(GUEST_SYSENTER_CS, vmcs12->guest_sysenter_cs);
10667 vmx_set_rflags(vcpu, vmcs12->guest_rflags);
10668 vmcs_writel(GUEST_PENDING_DBG_EXCEPTIONS,
10669 vmcs12->guest_pending_dbg_exceptions);
10670 vmcs_writel(GUEST_SYSENTER_ESP, vmcs12->guest_sysenter_esp);
10671 vmcs_writel(GUEST_SYSENTER_EIP, vmcs12->guest_sysenter_eip);
10672
10673 if (nested_cpu_has_xsaves(vmcs12))
10674 vmcs_write64(XSS_EXIT_BITMAP, vmcs12->xss_exit_bitmap);
10675 vmcs_write64(VMCS_LINK_POINTER, -1ull);
10676
10677 exec_control = vmcs12->pin_based_vm_exec_control;
10678
10679 /* Preemption timer setting is only taken from vmcs01. */
10680 exec_control &= ~PIN_BASED_VMX_PREEMPTION_TIMER;
10681 exec_control |= vmcs_config.pin_based_exec_ctrl;
10682 if (vmx->hv_deadline_tsc == -1)
10683 exec_control &= ~PIN_BASED_VMX_PREEMPTION_TIMER;
10684
10685 /* Posted interrupts setting is only taken from vmcs12. */
10686 if (nested_cpu_has_posted_intr(vmcs12)) {
10687 vmx->nested.posted_intr_nv = vmcs12->posted_intr_nv;
10688 vmx->nested.pi_pending = false;
10689 vmcs_write16(POSTED_INTR_NV, POSTED_INTR_NESTED_VECTOR);
10690 } else {
10691 exec_control &= ~PIN_BASED_POSTED_INTR;
10692 }
10693
10694 vmcs_write32(PIN_BASED_VM_EXEC_CONTROL, exec_control);
10695
10696 vmx->nested.preemption_timer_expired = false;
10697 if (nested_cpu_has_preemption_timer(vmcs12))
10698 vmx_start_preemption_timer(vcpu);
10699
10700 /*
10701 * Whether page-faults are trapped is determined by a combination of
10702 * 3 settings: PFEC_MASK, PFEC_MATCH and EXCEPTION_BITMAP.PF.
10703 * If enable_ept, L0 doesn't care about page faults and we should
10704 * set all of these to L1's desires. However, if !enable_ept, L0 does
10705 * care about (at least some) page faults, and because it is not easy
10706 * (if at all possible?) to merge L0 and L1's desires, we simply ask
10707 * to exit on each and every L2 page fault. This is done by setting
10708 * MASK=MATCH=0 and (see below) EB.PF=1.
10709 * Note that below we don't need special code to set EB.PF beyond the
10710 * "or"ing of the EB of vmcs01 and vmcs12, because when enable_ept,
10711 * vmcs01's EB.PF is 0 so the "or" will take vmcs12's value, and when
10712 * !enable_ept, EB.PF is 1, so the "or" will always be 1.
10713 */
10714 vmcs_write32(PAGE_FAULT_ERROR_CODE_MASK,
10715 enable_ept ? vmcs12->page_fault_error_code_mask : 0);
10716 vmcs_write32(PAGE_FAULT_ERROR_CODE_MATCH,
10717 enable_ept ? vmcs12->page_fault_error_code_match : 0);
10718
10719 if (cpu_has_secondary_exec_ctrls()) {
10720 exec_control = vmx->secondary_exec_control;
10721
10722 /* Take the following fields only from vmcs12 */
10723 exec_control &= ~(SECONDARY_EXEC_VIRTUALIZE_APIC_ACCESSES |
10724 SECONDARY_EXEC_ENABLE_INVPCID |
10725 SECONDARY_EXEC_RDTSCP |
10726 SECONDARY_EXEC_XSAVES |
10727 SECONDARY_EXEC_VIRTUAL_INTR_DELIVERY |
10728 SECONDARY_EXEC_APIC_REGISTER_VIRT |
10729 SECONDARY_EXEC_ENABLE_VMFUNC);
10730 if (nested_cpu_has(vmcs12,
10731 CPU_BASED_ACTIVATE_SECONDARY_CONTROLS)) {
10732 vmcs12_exec_ctrl = vmcs12->secondary_vm_exec_control &
10733 ~SECONDARY_EXEC_ENABLE_PML;
10734 exec_control |= vmcs12_exec_ctrl;
10735 }
10736
10737 /* All VMFUNCs are currently emulated through L0 vmexits. */
10738 if (exec_control & SECONDARY_EXEC_ENABLE_VMFUNC)
10739 vmcs_write64(VM_FUNCTION_CONTROL, 0);
10740
10741 if (exec_control & SECONDARY_EXEC_VIRTUAL_INTR_DELIVERY) {
10742 vmcs_write64(EOI_EXIT_BITMAP0,
10743 vmcs12->eoi_exit_bitmap0);
10744 vmcs_write64(EOI_EXIT_BITMAP1,
10745 vmcs12->eoi_exit_bitmap1);
10746 vmcs_write64(EOI_EXIT_BITMAP2,
10747 vmcs12->eoi_exit_bitmap2);
10748 vmcs_write64(EOI_EXIT_BITMAP3,
10749 vmcs12->eoi_exit_bitmap3);
10750 vmcs_write16(GUEST_INTR_STATUS,
10751 vmcs12->guest_intr_status);
10752 }
10753
10754 /*
10755 * Write an illegal value to APIC_ACCESS_ADDR. Later,
10756 * nested_get_vmcs12_pages will either fix it up or
10757 * remove the VM execution control.
10758 */
10759 if (exec_control & SECONDARY_EXEC_VIRTUALIZE_APIC_ACCESSES)
10760 vmcs_write64(APIC_ACCESS_ADDR, -1ull);
10761
10762 vmcs_write32(SECONDARY_VM_EXEC_CONTROL, exec_control);
10763 }
10764
10765
10766 /*
10767 * Set host-state according to L0's settings (vmcs12 is irrelevant here)
10768 * Some constant fields are set here by vmx_set_constant_host_state().
10769 * Other fields are different per CPU, and will be set later when
10770 * vmx_vcpu_load() is called, and when vmx_save_host_state() is called.
10771 */
10772 vmx_set_constant_host_state(vmx);
10773
10774 /*
10775 * Set the MSR load/store lists to match L0's settings.
10776 */
10777 vmcs_write32(VM_EXIT_MSR_STORE_COUNT, 0);
10778 vmcs_write32(VM_EXIT_MSR_LOAD_COUNT, vmx->msr_autoload.nr);
10779 vmcs_write64(VM_EXIT_MSR_LOAD_ADDR, __pa(vmx->msr_autoload.host));
10780 vmcs_write32(VM_ENTRY_MSR_LOAD_COUNT, vmx->msr_autoload.nr);
10781 vmcs_write64(VM_ENTRY_MSR_LOAD_ADDR, __pa(vmx->msr_autoload.guest));
10782
10783 /*
10784 * HOST_RSP is normally set correctly in vmx_vcpu_run() just before
10785 * entry, but only if the current (host) sp changed from the value
10786 * we wrote last (vmx->host_rsp). This cache is no longer relevant
10787 * if we switch vmcs, and rather than hold a separate cache per vmcs,
10788 * here we just force the write to happen on entry.
10789 */
10790 vmx->host_rsp = 0;
10791
10792 exec_control = vmx_exec_control(vmx); /* L0's desires */
10793 exec_control &= ~CPU_BASED_VIRTUAL_INTR_PENDING;
10794 exec_control &= ~CPU_BASED_VIRTUAL_NMI_PENDING;
10795 exec_control &= ~CPU_BASED_TPR_SHADOW;
10796 exec_control |= vmcs12->cpu_based_vm_exec_control;
10797
10798 /*
10799 * Write an illegal value to VIRTUAL_APIC_PAGE_ADDR. Later, if
10800 * nested_get_vmcs12_pages can't fix it up, the illegal value
10801 * will result in a VM entry failure.
10802 */
10803 if (exec_control & CPU_BASED_TPR_SHADOW) {
10804 vmcs_write64(VIRTUAL_APIC_PAGE_ADDR, -1ull);
10805 vmcs_write32(TPR_THRESHOLD, vmcs12->tpr_threshold);
10806 } else {
10807#ifdef CONFIG_X86_64
10808 exec_control |= CPU_BASED_CR8_LOAD_EXITING |
10809 CPU_BASED_CR8_STORE_EXITING;
10810#endif
10811 }
10812
10813 /*
10814 * Merging of IO bitmap not currently supported.
10815 * Rather, exit every time.
10816 */
10817 exec_control &= ~CPU_BASED_USE_IO_BITMAPS;
10818 exec_control |= CPU_BASED_UNCOND_IO_EXITING;
10819
10820 vmcs_write32(CPU_BASED_VM_EXEC_CONTROL, exec_control);
10821
10822 /* EXCEPTION_BITMAP and CR0_GUEST_HOST_MASK should basically be the
10823 * bitwise-or of what L1 wants to trap for L2, and what we want to
10824 * trap. Note that CR0.TS also needs updating - we do this later.
10825 */
10826 update_exception_bitmap(vcpu);
10827 vcpu->arch.cr0_guest_owned_bits &= ~vmcs12->cr0_guest_host_mask;
10828 vmcs_writel(CR0_GUEST_HOST_MASK, ~vcpu->arch.cr0_guest_owned_bits);
10829
10830 /* L2->L1 exit controls are emulated - the hardware exit is to L0 so
10831 * we should use its exit controls. Note that VM_EXIT_LOAD_IA32_EFER
10832 * bits are further modified by vmx_set_efer() below.
10833 */
10834 vmcs_write32(VM_EXIT_CONTROLS, vmcs_config.vmexit_ctrl);
10835
10836 /* vmcs12's VM_ENTRY_LOAD_IA32_EFER and VM_ENTRY_IA32E_MODE are
10837 * emulated by vmx_set_efer(), below.
10838 */
10839 vm_entry_controls_init(vmx,
10840 (vmcs12->vm_entry_controls & ~VM_ENTRY_LOAD_IA32_EFER &
10841 ~VM_ENTRY_IA32E_MODE) |
10842 (vmcs_config.vmentry_ctrl & ~VM_ENTRY_IA32E_MODE));
10843
10844 if (from_vmentry &&
10845 (vmcs12->vm_entry_controls & VM_ENTRY_LOAD_IA32_PAT)) {
10846 vmcs_write64(GUEST_IA32_PAT, vmcs12->guest_ia32_pat);
10847 vcpu->arch.pat = vmcs12->guest_ia32_pat;
10848 } else if (vmcs_config.vmentry_ctrl & VM_ENTRY_LOAD_IA32_PAT) {
10849 vmcs_write64(GUEST_IA32_PAT, vmx->vcpu.arch.pat);
10850 }
10851
10852 set_cr4_guest_host_mask(vmx);
10853
10854 if (from_vmentry &&
10855 vmcs12->vm_entry_controls & VM_ENTRY_LOAD_BNDCFGS)
10856 vmcs_write64(GUEST_BNDCFGS, vmcs12->guest_bndcfgs);
10857
10858 if (vmcs12->cpu_based_vm_exec_control & CPU_BASED_USE_TSC_OFFSETING)
10859 vmcs_write64(TSC_OFFSET,
10860 vcpu->arch.tsc_offset + vmcs12->tsc_offset);
10861 else
10862 vmcs_write64(TSC_OFFSET, vcpu->arch.tsc_offset);
10863 if (kvm_has_tsc_control)
10864 decache_tsc_multiplier(vmx);
10865
10866 if (cpu_has_vmx_msr_bitmap())
10867 vmcs_write64(MSR_BITMAP, __pa(vmx->nested.vmcs02.msr_bitmap));
10868
10869 if (enable_vpid) {
10870 /*
10871 * There is no direct mapping between vpid02 and vpid12, the
10872 * vpid02 is per-vCPU for L0 and reused while the value of
10873 * vpid12 is changed w/ one invvpid during nested vmentry.
10874 * The vpid12 is allocated by L1 for L2, so it will not
10875 * influence global bitmap(for vpid01 and vpid02 allocation)
10876 * even if spawn a lot of nested vCPUs.
10877 */
10878 if (nested_cpu_has_vpid(vmcs12) && vmx->nested.vpid02) {
10879 vmcs_write16(VIRTUAL_PROCESSOR_ID, vmx->nested.vpid02);
10880 if (vmcs12->virtual_processor_id != vmx->nested.last_vpid) {
10881 vmx->nested.last_vpid = vmcs12->virtual_processor_id;
10882 __vmx_flush_tlb(vcpu, to_vmx(vcpu)->nested.vpid02);
10883 }
10884 } else {
10885 vmcs_write16(VIRTUAL_PROCESSOR_ID, vmx->vpid);
10886 vmx_flush_tlb(vcpu);
10887 }
10888
10889 }
10890
10891 if (enable_pml) {
10892 /*
10893 * Conceptually we want to copy the PML address and index from
10894 * vmcs01 here, and then back to vmcs01 on nested vmexit. But,
10895 * since we always flush the log on each vmexit, this happens
10896 * to be equivalent to simply resetting the fields in vmcs02.
10897 */
10898 ASSERT(vmx->pml_pg);
10899 vmcs_write64(PML_ADDRESS, page_to_phys(vmx->pml_pg));
10900 vmcs_write16(GUEST_PML_INDEX, PML_ENTITY_NUM - 1);
10901 }
10902
10903 if (nested_cpu_has_ept(vmcs12)) {
10904 if (nested_ept_init_mmu_context(vcpu)) {
10905 *entry_failure_code = ENTRY_FAIL_DEFAULT;
10906 return 1;
10907 }
10908 } else if (nested_cpu_has2(vmcs12,
10909 SECONDARY_EXEC_VIRTUALIZE_APIC_ACCESSES)) {
10910 vmx_flush_tlb_ept_only(vcpu);
10911 }
10912
10913 /*
10914 * This sets GUEST_CR0 to vmcs12->guest_cr0, possibly modifying those
10915 * bits which we consider mandatory enabled.
10916 * The CR0_READ_SHADOW is what L2 should have expected to read given
10917 * the specifications by L1; It's not enough to take
10918 * vmcs12->cr0_read_shadow because on our cr0_guest_host_mask we we
10919 * have more bits than L1 expected.
10920 */
10921 vmx_set_cr0(vcpu, vmcs12->guest_cr0);
10922 vmcs_writel(CR0_READ_SHADOW, nested_read_cr0(vmcs12));
10923
10924 vmx_set_cr4(vcpu, vmcs12->guest_cr4);
10925 vmcs_writel(CR4_READ_SHADOW, nested_read_cr4(vmcs12));
10926
10927 if (from_vmentry &&
10928 (vmcs12->vm_entry_controls & VM_ENTRY_LOAD_IA32_EFER))
10929 vcpu->arch.efer = vmcs12->guest_ia32_efer;
10930 else if (vmcs12->vm_entry_controls & VM_ENTRY_IA32E_MODE)
10931 vcpu->arch.efer |= (EFER_LMA | EFER_LME);
10932 else
10933 vcpu->arch.efer &= ~(EFER_LMA | EFER_LME);
10934 /* Note: modifies VM_ENTRY/EXIT_CONTROLS and GUEST/HOST_IA32_EFER */
10935 vmx_set_efer(vcpu, vcpu->arch.efer);
10936
10937 /* Shadow page tables on either EPT or shadow page tables. */
10938 if (nested_vmx_load_cr3(vcpu, vmcs12->guest_cr3, nested_cpu_has_ept(vmcs12),
10939 entry_failure_code))
10940 return 1;
10941
10942 if (!enable_ept)
10943 vcpu->arch.walk_mmu->inject_page_fault = vmx_inject_page_fault_nested;
10944
10945 /*
10946 * L1 may access the L2's PDPTR, so save them to construct vmcs12
10947 */
10948 if (enable_ept) {
10949 vmcs_write64(GUEST_PDPTR0, vmcs12->guest_pdptr0);
10950 vmcs_write64(GUEST_PDPTR1, vmcs12->guest_pdptr1);
10951 vmcs_write64(GUEST_PDPTR2, vmcs12->guest_pdptr2);
10952 vmcs_write64(GUEST_PDPTR3, vmcs12->guest_pdptr3);
10953 }
10954
10955 kvm_register_write(vcpu, VCPU_REGS_RSP, vmcs12->guest_rsp);
10956 kvm_register_write(vcpu, VCPU_REGS_RIP, vmcs12->guest_rip);
10957 return 0;
10958}
10959
10960static int check_vmentry_prereqs(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu, struct vmcs12 *vmcs12)
10961{
10962 struct vcpu_vmx *vmx = to_vmx(vcpu);
10963
10964 if (vmcs12->guest_activity_state != GUEST_ACTIVITY_ACTIVE &&
10965 vmcs12->guest_activity_state != GUEST_ACTIVITY_HLT)
10966 return VMXERR_ENTRY_INVALID_CONTROL_FIELD;
10967
10968 if (nested_vmx_check_io_bitmap_controls(vcpu, vmcs12))
10969 return VMXERR_ENTRY_INVALID_CONTROL_FIELD;
10970
10971 if (nested_vmx_check_msr_bitmap_controls(vcpu, vmcs12))
10972 return VMXERR_ENTRY_INVALID_CONTROL_FIELD;
10973
10974 if (nested_vmx_check_apic_access_controls(vcpu, vmcs12))
10975 return VMXERR_ENTRY_INVALID_CONTROL_FIELD;
10976
10977 if (nested_vmx_check_tpr_shadow_controls(vcpu, vmcs12))
10978 return VMXERR_ENTRY_INVALID_CONTROL_FIELD;
10979
10980 if (nested_vmx_check_apicv_controls(vcpu, vmcs12))
10981 return VMXERR_ENTRY_INVALID_CONTROL_FIELD;
10982
10983 if (nested_vmx_check_msr_switch_controls(vcpu, vmcs12))
10984 return VMXERR_ENTRY_INVALID_CONTROL_FIELD;
10985
10986 if (nested_vmx_check_pml_controls(vcpu, vmcs12))
10987 return VMXERR_ENTRY_INVALID_CONTROL_FIELD;
10988
10989 if (!vmx_control_verify(vmcs12->cpu_based_vm_exec_control,
10990 vmx->nested.nested_vmx_procbased_ctls_low,
10991 vmx->nested.nested_vmx_procbased_ctls_high) ||
10992 (nested_cpu_has(vmcs12, CPU_BASED_ACTIVATE_SECONDARY_CONTROLS) &&
10993 !vmx_control_verify(vmcs12->secondary_vm_exec_control,
10994 vmx->nested.nested_vmx_secondary_ctls_low,
10995 vmx->nested.nested_vmx_secondary_ctls_high)) ||
10996 !vmx_control_verify(vmcs12->pin_based_vm_exec_control,
10997 vmx->nested.nested_vmx_pinbased_ctls_low,
10998 vmx->nested.nested_vmx_pinbased_ctls_high) ||
10999 !vmx_control_verify(vmcs12->vm_exit_controls,
11000 vmx->nested.nested_vmx_exit_ctls_low,
11001 vmx->nested.nested_vmx_exit_ctls_high) ||
11002 !vmx_control_verify(vmcs12->vm_entry_controls,
11003 vmx->nested.nested_vmx_entry_ctls_low,
11004 vmx->nested.nested_vmx_entry_ctls_high))
11005 return VMXERR_ENTRY_INVALID_CONTROL_FIELD;
11006
11007 if (nested_cpu_has_vmfunc(vmcs12)) {
11008 if (vmcs12->vm_function_control &
11009 ~vmx->nested.nested_vmx_vmfunc_controls)
11010 return VMXERR_ENTRY_INVALID_CONTROL_FIELD;
11011
11012 if (nested_cpu_has_eptp_switching(vmcs12)) {
11013 if (!nested_cpu_has_ept(vmcs12) ||
11014 !page_address_valid(vcpu, vmcs12->eptp_list_address))
11015 return VMXERR_ENTRY_INVALID_CONTROL_FIELD;
11016 }
11017 }
11018
11019 if (vmcs12->cr3_target_count > nested_cpu_vmx_misc_cr3_count(vcpu))
11020 return VMXERR_ENTRY_INVALID_CONTROL_FIELD;
11021
11022 if (!nested_host_cr0_valid(vcpu, vmcs12->host_cr0) ||
11023 !nested_host_cr4_valid(vcpu, vmcs12->host_cr4) ||
11024 !nested_cr3_valid(vcpu, vmcs12->host_cr3))
11025 return VMXERR_ENTRY_INVALID_HOST_STATE_FIELD;
11026
11027 return 0;
11028}
11029
11030static int check_vmentry_postreqs(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu, struct vmcs12 *vmcs12,
11031 u32 *exit_qual)
11032{
11033 bool ia32e;
11034
11035 *exit_qual = ENTRY_FAIL_DEFAULT;
11036
11037 if (!nested_guest_cr0_valid(vcpu, vmcs12->guest_cr0) ||
11038 !nested_guest_cr4_valid(vcpu, vmcs12->guest_cr4))
11039 return 1;
11040
11041 if (!nested_cpu_has2(vmcs12, SECONDARY_EXEC_SHADOW_VMCS) &&
11042 vmcs12->vmcs_link_pointer != -1ull) {
11043 *exit_qual = ENTRY_FAIL_VMCS_LINK_PTR;
11044 return 1;
11045 }
11046
11047 /*
11048 * If the load IA32_EFER VM-entry control is 1, the following checks
11049 * are performed on the field for the IA32_EFER MSR:
11050 * - Bits reserved in the IA32_EFER MSR must be 0.
11051 * - Bit 10 (corresponding to IA32_EFER.LMA) must equal the value of
11052 * the IA-32e mode guest VM-exit control. It must also be identical
11053 * to bit 8 (LME) if bit 31 in the CR0 field (corresponding to
11054 * CR0.PG) is 1.
11055 */
11056 if (to_vmx(vcpu)->nested.nested_run_pending &&
11057 (vmcs12->vm_entry_controls & VM_ENTRY_LOAD_IA32_EFER)) {
11058 ia32e = (vmcs12->vm_entry_controls & VM_ENTRY_IA32E_MODE) != 0;
11059 if (!kvm_valid_efer(vcpu, vmcs12->guest_ia32_efer) ||
11060 ia32e != !!(vmcs12->guest_ia32_efer & EFER_LMA) ||
11061 ((vmcs12->guest_cr0 & X86_CR0_PG) &&
11062 ia32e != !!(vmcs12->guest_ia32_efer & EFER_LME)))
11063 return 1;
11064 }
11065
11066 /*
11067 * If the load IA32_EFER VM-exit control is 1, bits reserved in the
11068 * IA32_EFER MSR must be 0 in the field for that register. In addition,
11069 * the values of the LMA and LME bits in the field must each be that of
11070 * the host address-space size VM-exit control.
11071 */
11072 if (vmcs12->vm_exit_controls & VM_EXIT_LOAD_IA32_EFER) {
11073 ia32e = (vmcs12->vm_exit_controls &
11074 VM_EXIT_HOST_ADDR_SPACE_SIZE) != 0;
11075 if (!kvm_valid_efer(vcpu, vmcs12->host_ia32_efer) ||
11076 ia32e != !!(vmcs12->host_ia32_efer & EFER_LMA) ||
11077 ia32e != !!(vmcs12->host_ia32_efer & EFER_LME))
11078 return 1;
11079 }
11080
11081 return 0;
11082}
11083
11084static int enter_vmx_non_root_mode(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu, bool from_vmentry)
11085{
11086 struct vcpu_vmx *vmx = to_vmx(vcpu);
11087 struct vmcs12 *vmcs12 = get_vmcs12(vcpu);
11088 u32 msr_entry_idx;
11089 u32 exit_qual;
11090
11091 enter_guest_mode(vcpu);
11092
11093 if (!(vmcs12->vm_entry_controls & VM_ENTRY_LOAD_DEBUG_CONTROLS))
11094 vmx->nested.vmcs01_debugctl = vmcs_read64(GUEST_IA32_DEBUGCTL);
11095
11096 vmx_switch_vmcs(vcpu, &vmx->nested.vmcs02);
11097 vmx_segment_cache_clear(vmx);
11098
11099 if (prepare_vmcs02(vcpu, vmcs12, from_vmentry, &exit_qual)) {
11100 leave_guest_mode(vcpu);
11101 vmx_switch_vmcs(vcpu, &vmx->vmcs01);
11102 nested_vmx_entry_failure(vcpu, vmcs12,
11103 EXIT_REASON_INVALID_STATE, exit_qual);
11104 return 1;
11105 }
11106
11107 nested_get_vmcs12_pages(vcpu, vmcs12);
11108
11109 msr_entry_idx = nested_vmx_load_msr(vcpu,
11110 vmcs12->vm_entry_msr_load_addr,
11111 vmcs12->vm_entry_msr_load_count);
11112 if (msr_entry_idx) {
11113 leave_guest_mode(vcpu);
11114 vmx_switch_vmcs(vcpu, &vmx->vmcs01);
11115 nested_vmx_entry_failure(vcpu, vmcs12,
11116 EXIT_REASON_MSR_LOAD_FAIL, msr_entry_idx);
11117 return 1;
11118 }
11119
11120 /*
11121 * Note no nested_vmx_succeed or nested_vmx_fail here. At this point
11122 * we are no longer running L1, and VMLAUNCH/VMRESUME has not yet
11123 * returned as far as L1 is concerned. It will only return (and set
11124 * the success flag) when L2 exits (see nested_vmx_vmexit()).
11125 */
11126 return 0;
11127}
11128
11129/*
11130 * nested_vmx_run() handles a nested entry, i.e., a VMLAUNCH or VMRESUME on L1
11131 * for running an L2 nested guest.
11132 */
11133static int nested_vmx_run(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu, bool launch)
11134{
11135 struct vmcs12 *vmcs12;
11136 struct vcpu_vmx *vmx = to_vmx(vcpu);
11137 u32 interrupt_shadow = vmx_get_interrupt_shadow(vcpu);
11138 u32 exit_qual;
11139 int ret;
11140
11141 if (!nested_vmx_check_permission(vcpu))
11142 return 1;
11143
11144 if (!nested_vmx_check_vmcs12(vcpu))
11145 goto out;
11146
11147 vmcs12 = get_vmcs12(vcpu);
11148
11149 if (enable_shadow_vmcs)
11150 copy_shadow_to_vmcs12(vmx);
11151
11152 /*
11153 * The nested entry process starts with enforcing various prerequisites
11154 * on vmcs12 as required by the Intel SDM, and act appropriately when
11155 * they fail: As the SDM explains, some conditions should cause the
11156 * instruction to fail, while others will cause the instruction to seem
11157 * to succeed, but return an EXIT_REASON_INVALID_STATE.
11158 * To speed up the normal (success) code path, we should avoid checking
11159 * for misconfigurations which will anyway be caught by the processor
11160 * when using the merged vmcs02.
11161 */
11162 if (interrupt_shadow & KVM_X86_SHADOW_INT_MOV_SS) {
11163 nested_vmx_failValid(vcpu,
11164 VMXERR_ENTRY_EVENTS_BLOCKED_BY_MOV_SS);
11165 goto out;
11166 }
11167
11168 if (vmcs12->launch_state == launch) {
11169 nested_vmx_failValid(vcpu,
11170 launch ? VMXERR_VMLAUNCH_NONCLEAR_VMCS
11171 : VMXERR_VMRESUME_NONLAUNCHED_VMCS);
11172 goto out;
11173 }
11174
11175 ret = check_vmentry_prereqs(vcpu, vmcs12);
11176 if (ret) {
11177 nested_vmx_failValid(vcpu, ret);
11178 goto out;
11179 }
11180
11181 /*
11182 * After this point, the trap flag no longer triggers a singlestep trap
11183 * on the vm entry instructions; don't call kvm_skip_emulated_instruction.
11184 * This is not 100% correct; for performance reasons, we delegate most
11185 * of the checks on host state to the processor. If those fail,
11186 * the singlestep trap is missed.
11187 */
11188 skip_emulated_instruction(vcpu);
11189
11190 ret = check_vmentry_postreqs(vcpu, vmcs12, &exit_qual);
11191 if (ret) {
11192 nested_vmx_entry_failure(vcpu, vmcs12,
11193 EXIT_REASON_INVALID_STATE, exit_qual);
11194 return 1;
11195 }
11196
11197 /*
11198 * We're finally done with prerequisite checking, and can start with
11199 * the nested entry.
11200 */
11201
11202 ret = enter_vmx_non_root_mode(vcpu, true);
11203 if (ret)
11204 return ret;
11205
11206 /*
11207 * If we're entering a halted L2 vcpu and the L2 vcpu won't be woken
11208 * by event injection, halt vcpu.
11209 */
11210 if ((vmcs12->guest_activity_state == GUEST_ACTIVITY_HLT) &&
11211 !(vmcs12->vm_entry_intr_info_field & INTR_INFO_VALID_MASK))
11212 return kvm_vcpu_halt(vcpu);
11213
11214 vmx->nested.nested_run_pending = 1;
11215
11216 return 1;
11217
11218out:
11219 return kvm_skip_emulated_instruction(vcpu);
11220}
11221
11222/*
11223 * On a nested exit from L2 to L1, vmcs12.guest_cr0 might not be up-to-date
11224 * because L2 may have changed some cr0 bits directly (CRO_GUEST_HOST_MASK).
11225 * This function returns the new value we should put in vmcs12.guest_cr0.
11226 * It's not enough to just return the vmcs02 GUEST_CR0. Rather,
11227 * 1. Bits that neither L0 nor L1 trapped, were set directly by L2 and are now
11228 * available in vmcs02 GUEST_CR0. (Note: It's enough to check that L0
11229 * didn't trap the bit, because if L1 did, so would L0).
11230 * 2. Bits that L1 asked to trap (and therefore L0 also did) could not have
11231 * been modified by L2, and L1 knows it. So just leave the old value of
11232 * the bit from vmcs12.guest_cr0. Note that the bit from vmcs02 GUEST_CR0
11233 * isn't relevant, because if L0 traps this bit it can set it to anything.
11234 * 3. Bits that L1 didn't trap, but L0 did. L1 believes the guest could have
11235 * changed these bits, and therefore they need to be updated, but L0
11236 * didn't necessarily allow them to be changed in GUEST_CR0 - and rather
11237 * put them in vmcs02 CR0_READ_SHADOW. So take these bits from there.
11238 */
11239static inline unsigned long
11240vmcs12_guest_cr0(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu, struct vmcs12 *vmcs12)
11241{
11242 return
11243 /*1*/ (vmcs_readl(GUEST_CR0) & vcpu->arch.cr0_guest_owned_bits) |
11244 /*2*/ (vmcs12->guest_cr0 & vmcs12->cr0_guest_host_mask) |
11245 /*3*/ (vmcs_readl(CR0_READ_SHADOW) & ~(vmcs12->cr0_guest_host_mask |
11246 vcpu->arch.cr0_guest_owned_bits));
11247}
11248
11249static inline unsigned long
11250vmcs12_guest_cr4(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu, struct vmcs12 *vmcs12)
11251{
11252 return
11253 /*1*/ (vmcs_readl(GUEST_CR4) & vcpu->arch.cr4_guest_owned_bits) |
11254 /*2*/ (vmcs12->guest_cr4 & vmcs12->cr4_guest_host_mask) |
11255 /*3*/ (vmcs_readl(CR4_READ_SHADOW) & ~(vmcs12->cr4_guest_host_mask |
11256 vcpu->arch.cr4_guest_owned_bits));
11257}
11258
11259static void vmcs12_save_pending_event(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu,
11260 struct vmcs12 *vmcs12)
11261{
11262 u32 idt_vectoring;
11263 unsigned int nr;
11264
11265 if (vcpu->arch.exception.injected) {
11266 nr = vcpu->arch.exception.nr;
11267 idt_vectoring = nr | VECTORING_INFO_VALID_MASK;
11268
11269 if (kvm_exception_is_soft(nr)) {
11270 vmcs12->vm_exit_instruction_len =
11271 vcpu->arch.event_exit_inst_len;
11272 idt_vectoring |= INTR_TYPE_SOFT_EXCEPTION;
11273 } else
11274 idt_vectoring |= INTR_TYPE_HARD_EXCEPTION;
11275
11276 if (vcpu->arch.exception.has_error_code) {
11277 idt_vectoring |= VECTORING_INFO_DELIVER_CODE_MASK;
11278 vmcs12->idt_vectoring_error_code =
11279 vcpu->arch.exception.error_code;
11280 }
11281
11282 vmcs12->idt_vectoring_info_field = idt_vectoring;
11283 } else if (vcpu->arch.nmi_injected) {
11284 vmcs12->idt_vectoring_info_field =
11285 INTR_TYPE_NMI_INTR | INTR_INFO_VALID_MASK | NMI_VECTOR;
11286 } else if (vcpu->arch.interrupt.pending) {
11287 nr = vcpu->arch.interrupt.nr;
11288 idt_vectoring = nr | VECTORING_INFO_VALID_MASK;
11289
11290 if (vcpu->arch.interrupt.soft) {
11291 idt_vectoring |= INTR_TYPE_SOFT_INTR;
11292 vmcs12->vm_entry_instruction_len =
11293 vcpu->arch.event_exit_inst_len;
11294 } else
11295 idt_vectoring |= INTR_TYPE_EXT_INTR;
11296
11297 vmcs12->idt_vectoring_info_field = idt_vectoring;
11298 }
11299}
11300
11301static int vmx_check_nested_events(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu, bool external_intr)
11302{
11303 struct vcpu_vmx *vmx = to_vmx(vcpu);
11304 unsigned long exit_qual;
11305 bool block_nested_events =
11306 vmx->nested.nested_run_pending || kvm_event_needs_reinjection(vcpu);
11307
11308 if (vcpu->arch.exception.pending &&
11309 nested_vmx_check_exception(vcpu, &exit_qual)) {
11310 if (block_nested_events)
11311 return -EBUSY;
11312 nested_vmx_inject_exception_vmexit(vcpu, exit_qual);
11313 return 0;
11314 }
11315
11316 if (nested_cpu_has_preemption_timer(get_vmcs12(vcpu)) &&
11317 vmx->nested.preemption_timer_expired) {
11318 if (block_nested_events)
11319 return -EBUSY;
11320 nested_vmx_vmexit(vcpu, EXIT_REASON_PREEMPTION_TIMER, 0, 0);
11321 return 0;
11322 }
11323
11324 if (vcpu->arch.nmi_pending && nested_exit_on_nmi(vcpu)) {
11325 if (block_nested_events)
11326 return -EBUSY;
11327 nested_vmx_vmexit(vcpu, EXIT_REASON_EXCEPTION_NMI,
11328 NMI_VECTOR | INTR_TYPE_NMI_INTR |
11329 INTR_INFO_VALID_MASK, 0);
11330 /*
11331 * The NMI-triggered VM exit counts as injection:
11332 * clear this one and block further NMIs.
11333 */
11334 vcpu->arch.nmi_pending = 0;
11335 vmx_set_nmi_mask(vcpu, true);
11336 return 0;
11337 }
11338
11339 if ((kvm_cpu_has_interrupt(vcpu) || external_intr) &&
11340 nested_exit_on_intr(vcpu)) {
11341 if (block_nested_events)
11342 return -EBUSY;
11343 nested_vmx_vmexit(vcpu, EXIT_REASON_EXTERNAL_INTERRUPT, 0, 0);
11344 return 0;
11345 }
11346
11347 vmx_complete_nested_posted_interrupt(vcpu);
11348 return 0;
11349}
11350
11351static u32 vmx_get_preemption_timer_value(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu)
11352{
11353 ktime_t remaining =
11354 hrtimer_get_remaining(&to_vmx(vcpu)->nested.preemption_timer);
11355 u64 value;
11356
11357 if (ktime_to_ns(remaining) <= 0)
11358 return 0;
11359
11360 value = ktime_to_ns(remaining) * vcpu->arch.virtual_tsc_khz;
11361 do_div(value, 1000000);
11362 return value >> VMX_MISC_EMULATED_PREEMPTION_TIMER_RATE;
11363}
11364
11365/*
11366 * Update the guest state fields of vmcs12 to reflect changes that
11367 * occurred while L2 was running. (The "IA-32e mode guest" bit of the
11368 * VM-entry controls is also updated, since this is really a guest
11369 * state bit.)
11370 */
11371static void sync_vmcs12(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu, struct vmcs12 *vmcs12)
11372{
11373 vmcs12->guest_cr0 = vmcs12_guest_cr0(vcpu, vmcs12);
11374 vmcs12->guest_cr4 = vmcs12_guest_cr4(vcpu, vmcs12);
11375
11376 vmcs12->guest_rsp = kvm_register_read(vcpu, VCPU_REGS_RSP);
11377 vmcs12->guest_rip = kvm_register_read(vcpu, VCPU_REGS_RIP);
11378 vmcs12->guest_rflags = vmcs_readl(GUEST_RFLAGS);
11379
11380 vmcs12->guest_es_selector = vmcs_read16(GUEST_ES_SELECTOR);
11381 vmcs12->guest_cs_selector = vmcs_read16(GUEST_CS_SELECTOR);
11382 vmcs12->guest_ss_selector = vmcs_read16(GUEST_SS_SELECTOR);
11383 vmcs12->guest_ds_selector = vmcs_read16(GUEST_DS_SELECTOR);
11384 vmcs12->guest_fs_selector = vmcs_read16(GUEST_FS_SELECTOR);
11385 vmcs12->guest_gs_selector = vmcs_read16(GUEST_GS_SELECTOR);
11386 vmcs12->guest_ldtr_selector = vmcs_read16(GUEST_LDTR_SELECTOR);
11387 vmcs12->guest_tr_selector = vmcs_read16(GUEST_TR_SELECTOR);
11388 vmcs12->guest_es_limit = vmcs_read32(GUEST_ES_LIMIT);
11389 vmcs12->guest_cs_limit = vmcs_read32(GUEST_CS_LIMIT);
11390 vmcs12->guest_ss_limit = vmcs_read32(GUEST_SS_LIMIT);
11391 vmcs12->guest_ds_limit = vmcs_read32(GUEST_DS_LIMIT);
11392 vmcs12->guest_fs_limit = vmcs_read32(GUEST_FS_LIMIT);
11393 vmcs12->guest_gs_limit = vmcs_read32(GUEST_GS_LIMIT);
11394 vmcs12->guest_ldtr_limit = vmcs_read32(GUEST_LDTR_LIMIT);
11395 vmcs12->guest_tr_limit = vmcs_read32(GUEST_TR_LIMIT);
11396 vmcs12->guest_gdtr_limit = vmcs_read32(GUEST_GDTR_LIMIT);
11397 vmcs12->guest_idtr_limit = vmcs_read32(GUEST_IDTR_LIMIT);
11398 vmcs12->guest_es_ar_bytes = vmcs_read32(GUEST_ES_AR_BYTES);
11399 vmcs12->guest_cs_ar_bytes = vmcs_read32(GUEST_CS_AR_BYTES);
11400 vmcs12->guest_ss_ar_bytes = vmcs_read32(GUEST_SS_AR_BYTES);
11401 vmcs12->guest_ds_ar_bytes = vmcs_read32(GUEST_DS_AR_BYTES);
11402 vmcs12->guest_fs_ar_bytes = vmcs_read32(GUEST_FS_AR_BYTES);
11403 vmcs12->guest_gs_ar_bytes = vmcs_read32(GUEST_GS_AR_BYTES);
11404 vmcs12->guest_ldtr_ar_bytes = vmcs_read32(GUEST_LDTR_AR_BYTES);
11405 vmcs12->guest_tr_ar_bytes = vmcs_read32(GUEST_TR_AR_BYTES);
11406 vmcs12->guest_es_base = vmcs_readl(GUEST_ES_BASE);
11407 vmcs12->guest_cs_base = vmcs_readl(GUEST_CS_BASE);
11408 vmcs12->guest_ss_base = vmcs_readl(GUEST_SS_BASE);
11409 vmcs12->guest_ds_base = vmcs_readl(GUEST_DS_BASE);
11410 vmcs12->guest_fs_base = vmcs_readl(GUEST_FS_BASE);
11411 vmcs12->guest_gs_base = vmcs_readl(GUEST_GS_BASE);
11412 vmcs12->guest_ldtr_base = vmcs_readl(GUEST_LDTR_BASE);
11413 vmcs12->guest_tr_base = vmcs_readl(GUEST_TR_BASE);
11414 vmcs12->guest_gdtr_base = vmcs_readl(GUEST_GDTR_BASE);
11415 vmcs12->guest_idtr_base = vmcs_readl(GUEST_IDTR_BASE);
11416
11417 vmcs12->guest_interruptibility_info =
11418 vmcs_read32(GUEST_INTERRUPTIBILITY_INFO);
11419 vmcs12->guest_pending_dbg_exceptions =
11420 vmcs_readl(GUEST_PENDING_DBG_EXCEPTIONS);
11421 if (vcpu->arch.mp_state == KVM_MP_STATE_HALTED)
11422 vmcs12->guest_activity_state = GUEST_ACTIVITY_HLT;
11423 else
11424 vmcs12->guest_activity_state = GUEST_ACTIVITY_ACTIVE;
11425
11426 if (nested_cpu_has_preemption_timer(vmcs12)) {
11427 if (vmcs12->vm_exit_controls &
11428 VM_EXIT_SAVE_VMX_PREEMPTION_TIMER)
11429 vmcs12->vmx_preemption_timer_value =
11430 vmx_get_preemption_timer_value(vcpu);
11431 hrtimer_cancel(&to_vmx(vcpu)->nested.preemption_timer);
11432 }
11433
11434 /*
11435 * In some cases (usually, nested EPT), L2 is allowed to change its
11436 * own CR3 without exiting. If it has changed it, we must keep it.
11437 * Of course, if L0 is using shadow page tables, GUEST_CR3 was defined
11438 * by L0, not L1 or L2, so we mustn't unconditionally copy it to vmcs12.
11439 *
11440 * Additionally, restore L2's PDPTR to vmcs12.
11441 */
11442 if (enable_ept) {
11443 vmcs12->guest_cr3 = vmcs_readl(GUEST_CR3);
11444 vmcs12->guest_pdptr0 = vmcs_read64(GUEST_PDPTR0);
11445 vmcs12->guest_pdptr1 = vmcs_read64(GUEST_PDPTR1);
11446 vmcs12->guest_pdptr2 = vmcs_read64(GUEST_PDPTR2);
11447 vmcs12->guest_pdptr3 = vmcs_read64(GUEST_PDPTR3);
11448 }
11449
11450 vmcs12->guest_linear_address = vmcs_readl(GUEST_LINEAR_ADDRESS);
11451
11452 if (nested_cpu_has_vid(vmcs12))
11453 vmcs12->guest_intr_status = vmcs_read16(GUEST_INTR_STATUS);
11454
11455 vmcs12->vm_entry_controls =
11456 (vmcs12->vm_entry_controls & ~VM_ENTRY_IA32E_MODE) |
11457 (vm_entry_controls_get(to_vmx(vcpu)) & VM_ENTRY_IA32E_MODE);
11458
11459 if (vmcs12->vm_exit_controls & VM_EXIT_SAVE_DEBUG_CONTROLS) {
11460 kvm_get_dr(vcpu, 7, (unsigned long *)&vmcs12->guest_dr7);
11461 vmcs12->guest_ia32_debugctl = vmcs_read64(GUEST_IA32_DEBUGCTL);
11462 }
11463
11464 /* TODO: These cannot have changed unless we have MSR bitmaps and
11465 * the relevant bit asks not to trap the change */
11466 if (vmcs12->vm_exit_controls & VM_EXIT_SAVE_IA32_PAT)
11467 vmcs12->guest_ia32_pat = vmcs_read64(GUEST_IA32_PAT);
11468 if (vmcs12->vm_exit_controls & VM_EXIT_SAVE_IA32_EFER)
11469 vmcs12->guest_ia32_efer = vcpu->arch.efer;
11470 vmcs12->guest_sysenter_cs = vmcs_read32(GUEST_SYSENTER_CS);
11471 vmcs12->guest_sysenter_esp = vmcs_readl(GUEST_SYSENTER_ESP);
11472 vmcs12->guest_sysenter_eip = vmcs_readl(GUEST_SYSENTER_EIP);
11473 if (kvm_mpx_supported())
11474 vmcs12->guest_bndcfgs = vmcs_read64(GUEST_BNDCFGS);
11475}
11476
11477/*
11478 * prepare_vmcs12 is part of what we need to do when the nested L2 guest exits
11479 * and we want to prepare to run its L1 parent. L1 keeps a vmcs for L2 (vmcs12),
11480 * and this function updates it to reflect the changes to the guest state while
11481 * L2 was running (and perhaps made some exits which were handled directly by L0
11482 * without going back to L1), and to reflect the exit reason.
11483 * Note that we do not have to copy here all VMCS fields, just those that
11484 * could have changed by the L2 guest or the exit - i.e., the guest-state and
11485 * exit-information fields only. Other fields are modified by L1 with VMWRITE,
11486 * which already writes to vmcs12 directly.
11487 */
11488static void prepare_vmcs12(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu, struct vmcs12 *vmcs12,
11489 u32 exit_reason, u32 exit_intr_info,
11490 unsigned long exit_qualification)
11491{
11492 /* update guest state fields: */
11493 sync_vmcs12(vcpu, vmcs12);
11494
11495 /* update exit information fields: */
11496
11497 vmcs12->vm_exit_reason = exit_reason;
11498 vmcs12->exit_qualification = exit_qualification;
11499 vmcs12->vm_exit_intr_info = exit_intr_info;
11500
11501 vmcs12->idt_vectoring_info_field = 0;
11502 vmcs12->vm_exit_instruction_len = vmcs_read32(VM_EXIT_INSTRUCTION_LEN);
11503 vmcs12->vmx_instruction_info = vmcs_read32(VMX_INSTRUCTION_INFO);
11504
11505 if (!(vmcs12->vm_exit_reason & VMX_EXIT_REASONS_FAILED_VMENTRY)) {
11506 vmcs12->launch_state = 1;
11507
11508 /* vm_entry_intr_info_field is cleared on exit. Emulate this
11509 * instead of reading the real value. */
11510 vmcs12->vm_entry_intr_info_field &= ~INTR_INFO_VALID_MASK;
11511
11512 /*
11513 * Transfer the event that L0 or L1 may wanted to inject into
11514 * L2 to IDT_VECTORING_INFO_FIELD.
11515 */
11516 vmcs12_save_pending_event(vcpu, vmcs12);
11517 }
11518
11519 /*
11520 * Drop what we picked up for L2 via vmx_complete_interrupts. It is
11521 * preserved above and would only end up incorrectly in L1.
11522 */
11523 vcpu->arch.nmi_injected = false;
11524 kvm_clear_exception_queue(vcpu);
11525 kvm_clear_interrupt_queue(vcpu);
11526}
11527
11528static void load_vmcs12_mmu_host_state(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu,
11529 struct vmcs12 *vmcs12)
11530{
11531 u32 entry_failure_code;
11532
11533 nested_ept_uninit_mmu_context(vcpu);
11534
11535 /*
11536 * Only PDPTE load can fail as the value of cr3 was checked on entry and
11537 * couldn't have changed.
11538 */
11539 if (nested_vmx_load_cr3(vcpu, vmcs12->host_cr3, false, &entry_failure_code))
11540 nested_vmx_abort(vcpu, VMX_ABORT_LOAD_HOST_PDPTE_FAIL);
11541
11542 if (!enable_ept)
11543 vcpu->arch.walk_mmu->inject_page_fault = kvm_inject_page_fault;
11544}
11545
11546/*
11547 * A part of what we need to when the nested L2 guest exits and we want to
11548 * run its L1 parent, is to reset L1's guest state to the host state specified
11549 * in vmcs12.
11550 * This function is to be called not only on normal nested exit, but also on
11551 * a nested entry failure, as explained in Intel's spec, 3B.23.7 ("VM-Entry
11552 * Failures During or After Loading Guest State").
11553 * This function should be called when the active VMCS is L1's (vmcs01).
11554 */
11555static void load_vmcs12_host_state(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu,
11556 struct vmcs12 *vmcs12)
11557{
11558 struct kvm_segment seg;
11559
11560 if (vmcs12->vm_exit_controls & VM_EXIT_LOAD_IA32_EFER)
11561 vcpu->arch.efer = vmcs12->host_ia32_efer;
11562 else if (vmcs12->vm_exit_controls & VM_EXIT_HOST_ADDR_SPACE_SIZE)
11563 vcpu->arch.efer |= (EFER_LMA | EFER_LME);
11564 else
11565 vcpu->arch.efer &= ~(EFER_LMA | EFER_LME);
11566 vmx_set_efer(vcpu, vcpu->arch.efer);
11567
11568 kvm_register_write(vcpu, VCPU_REGS_RSP, vmcs12->host_rsp);
11569 kvm_register_write(vcpu, VCPU_REGS_RIP, vmcs12->host_rip);
11570 vmx_set_rflags(vcpu, X86_EFLAGS_FIXED);
11571 /*
11572 * Note that calling vmx_set_cr0 is important, even if cr0 hasn't
11573 * actually changed, because vmx_set_cr0 refers to efer set above.
11574 *
11575 * CR0_GUEST_HOST_MASK is already set in the original vmcs01
11576 * (KVM doesn't change it);
11577 */
11578 vcpu->arch.cr0_guest_owned_bits = X86_CR0_TS;
11579 vmx_set_cr0(vcpu, vmcs12->host_cr0);
11580
11581 /* Same as above - no reason to call set_cr4_guest_host_mask(). */
11582 vcpu->arch.cr4_guest_owned_bits = ~vmcs_readl(CR4_GUEST_HOST_MASK);
11583 vmx_set_cr4(vcpu, vmcs12->host_cr4);
11584
11585 load_vmcs12_mmu_host_state(vcpu, vmcs12);
11586
11587 if (enable_vpid) {
11588 /*
11589 * Trivially support vpid by letting L2s share their parent
11590 * L1's vpid. TODO: move to a more elaborate solution, giving
11591 * each L2 its own vpid and exposing the vpid feature to L1.
11592 */
11593 vmx_flush_tlb(vcpu);
11594 }
11595 /* Restore posted intr vector. */
11596 if (nested_cpu_has_posted_intr(vmcs12))
11597 vmcs_write16(POSTED_INTR_NV, POSTED_INTR_VECTOR);
11598
11599 vmcs_write32(GUEST_SYSENTER_CS, vmcs12->host_ia32_sysenter_cs);
11600 vmcs_writel(GUEST_SYSENTER_ESP, vmcs12->host_ia32_sysenter_esp);
11601 vmcs_writel(GUEST_SYSENTER_EIP, vmcs12->host_ia32_sysenter_eip);
11602 vmcs_writel(GUEST_IDTR_BASE, vmcs12->host_idtr_base);
11603 vmcs_writel(GUEST_GDTR_BASE, vmcs12->host_gdtr_base);
11604 vmcs_write32(GUEST_IDTR_LIMIT, 0xFFFF);
11605 vmcs_write32(GUEST_GDTR_LIMIT, 0xFFFF);
11606
11607 /* If not VM_EXIT_CLEAR_BNDCFGS, the L2 value propagates to L1. */
11608 if (vmcs12->vm_exit_controls & VM_EXIT_CLEAR_BNDCFGS)
11609 vmcs_write64(GUEST_BNDCFGS, 0);
11610
11611 if (vmcs12->vm_exit_controls & VM_EXIT_LOAD_IA32_PAT) {
11612 vmcs_write64(GUEST_IA32_PAT, vmcs12->host_ia32_pat);
11613 vcpu->arch.pat = vmcs12->host_ia32_pat;
11614 }
11615 if (vmcs12->vm_exit_controls & VM_EXIT_LOAD_IA32_PERF_GLOBAL_CTRL)
11616 vmcs_write64(GUEST_IA32_PERF_GLOBAL_CTRL,
11617 vmcs12->host_ia32_perf_global_ctrl);
11618
11619 /* Set L1 segment info according to Intel SDM
11620 27.5.2 Loading Host Segment and Descriptor-Table Registers */
11621 seg = (struct kvm_segment) {
11622 .base = 0,
11623 .limit = 0xFFFFFFFF,
11624 .selector = vmcs12->host_cs_selector,
11625 .type = 11,
11626 .present = 1,
11627 .s = 1,
11628 .g = 1
11629 };
11630 if (vmcs12->vm_exit_controls & VM_EXIT_HOST_ADDR_SPACE_SIZE)
11631 seg.l = 1;
11632 else
11633 seg.db = 1;
11634 vmx_set_segment(vcpu, &seg, VCPU_SREG_CS);
11635 seg = (struct kvm_segment) {
11636 .base = 0,
11637 .limit = 0xFFFFFFFF,
11638 .type = 3,
11639 .present = 1,
11640 .s = 1,
11641 .db = 1,
11642 .g = 1
11643 };
11644 seg.selector = vmcs12->host_ds_selector;
11645 vmx_set_segment(vcpu, &seg, VCPU_SREG_DS);
11646 seg.selector = vmcs12->host_es_selector;
11647 vmx_set_segment(vcpu, &seg, VCPU_SREG_ES);
11648 seg.selector = vmcs12->host_ss_selector;
11649 vmx_set_segment(vcpu, &seg, VCPU_SREG_SS);
11650 seg.selector = vmcs12->host_fs_selector;
11651 seg.base = vmcs12->host_fs_base;
11652 vmx_set_segment(vcpu, &seg, VCPU_SREG_FS);
11653 seg.selector = vmcs12->host_gs_selector;
11654 seg.base = vmcs12->host_gs_base;
11655 vmx_set_segment(vcpu, &seg, VCPU_SREG_GS);
11656 seg = (struct kvm_segment) {
11657 .base = vmcs12->host_tr_base,
11658 .limit = 0x67,
11659 .selector = vmcs12->host_tr_selector,
11660 .type = 11,
11661 .present = 1
11662 };
11663 vmx_set_segment(vcpu, &seg, VCPU_SREG_TR);
11664
11665 kvm_set_dr(vcpu, 7, 0x400);
11666 vmcs_write64(GUEST_IA32_DEBUGCTL, 0);
11667
11668 if (cpu_has_vmx_msr_bitmap())
11669 vmx_update_msr_bitmap(vcpu);
11670
11671 if (nested_vmx_load_msr(vcpu, vmcs12->vm_exit_msr_load_addr,
11672 vmcs12->vm_exit_msr_load_count))
11673 nested_vmx_abort(vcpu, VMX_ABORT_LOAD_HOST_MSR_FAIL);
11674}
11675
11676/*
11677 * Emulate an exit from nested guest (L2) to L1, i.e., prepare to run L1
11678 * and modify vmcs12 to make it see what it would expect to see there if
11679 * L2 was its real guest. Must only be called when in L2 (is_guest_mode())
11680 */
11681static void nested_vmx_vmexit(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu, u32 exit_reason,
11682 u32 exit_intr_info,
11683 unsigned long exit_qualification)
11684{
11685 struct vcpu_vmx *vmx = to_vmx(vcpu);
11686 struct vmcs12 *vmcs12 = get_vmcs12(vcpu);
11687
11688 /* trying to cancel vmlaunch/vmresume is a bug */
11689 WARN_ON_ONCE(vmx->nested.nested_run_pending);
11690
11691 /*
11692 * The only expected VM-instruction error is "VM entry with
11693 * invalid control field(s)." Anything else indicates a
11694 * problem with L0.
11695 */
11696 WARN_ON_ONCE(vmx->fail && (vmcs_read32(VM_INSTRUCTION_ERROR) !=
11697 VMXERR_ENTRY_INVALID_CONTROL_FIELD));
11698
11699 leave_guest_mode(vcpu);
11700
11701 if (likely(!vmx->fail)) {
11702 prepare_vmcs12(vcpu, vmcs12, exit_reason, exit_intr_info,
11703 exit_qualification);
11704
11705 if (nested_vmx_store_msr(vcpu, vmcs12->vm_exit_msr_store_addr,
11706 vmcs12->vm_exit_msr_store_count))
11707 nested_vmx_abort(vcpu, VMX_ABORT_SAVE_GUEST_MSR_FAIL);
11708 }
11709
11710 vmx_switch_vmcs(vcpu, &vmx->vmcs01);
11711 vm_entry_controls_reset_shadow(vmx);
11712 vm_exit_controls_reset_shadow(vmx);
11713 vmx_segment_cache_clear(vmx);
11714
11715 /* Update any VMCS fields that might have changed while L2 ran */
11716 vmcs_write32(VM_EXIT_MSR_LOAD_COUNT, vmx->msr_autoload.nr);
11717 vmcs_write32(VM_ENTRY_MSR_LOAD_COUNT, vmx->msr_autoload.nr);
11718 vmcs_write64(TSC_OFFSET, vcpu->arch.tsc_offset);
11719 if (vmx->hv_deadline_tsc == -1)
11720 vmcs_clear_bits(PIN_BASED_VM_EXEC_CONTROL,
11721 PIN_BASED_VMX_PREEMPTION_TIMER);
11722 else
11723 vmcs_set_bits(PIN_BASED_VM_EXEC_CONTROL,
11724 PIN_BASED_VMX_PREEMPTION_TIMER);
11725 if (kvm_has_tsc_control)
11726 decache_tsc_multiplier(vmx);
11727
11728 if (vmx->nested.change_vmcs01_virtual_x2apic_mode) {
11729 vmx->nested.change_vmcs01_virtual_x2apic_mode = false;
11730 vmx_set_virtual_x2apic_mode(vcpu,
11731 vcpu->arch.apic_base & X2APIC_ENABLE);
11732 } else if (!nested_cpu_has_ept(vmcs12) &&
11733 nested_cpu_has2(vmcs12,
11734 SECONDARY_EXEC_VIRTUALIZE_APIC_ACCESSES)) {
11735 vmx_flush_tlb_ept_only(vcpu);
11736 }
11737
11738 /* This is needed for same reason as it was needed in prepare_vmcs02 */
11739 vmx->host_rsp = 0;
11740
11741 /* Unpin physical memory we referred to in vmcs02 */
11742 if (vmx->nested.apic_access_page) {
11743 kvm_release_page_dirty(vmx->nested.apic_access_page);
11744 vmx->nested.apic_access_page = NULL;
11745 }
11746 if (vmx->nested.virtual_apic_page) {
11747 kvm_release_page_dirty(vmx->nested.virtual_apic_page);
11748 vmx->nested.virtual_apic_page = NULL;
11749 }
11750 if (vmx->nested.pi_desc_page) {
11751 kunmap(vmx->nested.pi_desc_page);
11752 kvm_release_page_dirty(vmx->nested.pi_desc_page);
11753 vmx->nested.pi_desc_page = NULL;
11754 vmx->nested.pi_desc = NULL;
11755 }
11756
11757 /*
11758 * We are now running in L2, mmu_notifier will force to reload the
11759 * page's hpa for L2 vmcs. Need to reload it for L1 before entering L1.
11760 */
11761 kvm_make_request(KVM_REQ_APIC_PAGE_RELOAD, vcpu);
11762
11763 if (enable_shadow_vmcs)
11764 vmx->nested.sync_shadow_vmcs = true;
11765
11766 /* in case we halted in L2 */
11767 vcpu->arch.mp_state = KVM_MP_STATE_RUNNABLE;
11768
11769 if (likely(!vmx->fail)) {
11770 /*
11771 * TODO: SDM says that with acknowledge interrupt on
11772 * exit, bit 31 of the VM-exit interrupt information
11773 * (valid interrupt) is always set to 1 on
11774 * EXIT_REASON_EXTERNAL_INTERRUPT, so we shouldn't
11775 * need kvm_cpu_has_interrupt(). See the commit
11776 * message for details.
11777 */
11778 if (nested_exit_intr_ack_set(vcpu) &&
11779 exit_reason == EXIT_REASON_EXTERNAL_INTERRUPT &&
11780 kvm_cpu_has_interrupt(vcpu)) {
11781 int irq = kvm_cpu_get_interrupt(vcpu);
11782 WARN_ON(irq < 0);
11783 vmcs12->vm_exit_intr_info = irq |
11784 INTR_INFO_VALID_MASK | INTR_TYPE_EXT_INTR;
11785 }
11786
11787 trace_kvm_nested_vmexit_inject(vmcs12->vm_exit_reason,
11788 vmcs12->exit_qualification,
11789 vmcs12->idt_vectoring_info_field,
11790 vmcs12->vm_exit_intr_info,
11791 vmcs12->vm_exit_intr_error_code,
11792 KVM_ISA_VMX);
11793
11794 load_vmcs12_host_state(vcpu, vmcs12);
11795
11796 return;
11797 }
11798
11799 /*
11800 * After an early L2 VM-entry failure, we're now back
11801 * in L1 which thinks it just finished a VMLAUNCH or
11802 * VMRESUME instruction, so we need to set the failure
11803 * flag and the VM-instruction error field of the VMCS
11804 * accordingly.
11805 */
11806 nested_vmx_failValid(vcpu, VMXERR_ENTRY_INVALID_CONTROL_FIELD);
11807
11808 load_vmcs12_mmu_host_state(vcpu, vmcs12);
11809
11810 /*
11811 * The emulated instruction was already skipped in
11812 * nested_vmx_run, but the updated RIP was never
11813 * written back to the vmcs01.
11814 */
11815 skip_emulated_instruction(vcpu);
11816 vmx->fail = 0;
11817}
11818
11819/*
11820 * Forcibly leave nested mode in order to be able to reset the VCPU later on.
11821 */
11822static void vmx_leave_nested(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu)
11823{
11824 if (is_guest_mode(vcpu)) {
11825 to_vmx(vcpu)->nested.nested_run_pending = 0;
11826 nested_vmx_vmexit(vcpu, -1, 0, 0);
11827 }
11828 free_nested(to_vmx(vcpu));
11829}
11830
11831/*
11832 * L1's failure to enter L2 is a subset of a normal exit, as explained in
11833 * 23.7 "VM-entry failures during or after loading guest state" (this also
11834 * lists the acceptable exit-reason and exit-qualification parameters).
11835 * It should only be called before L2 actually succeeded to run, and when
11836 * vmcs01 is current (it doesn't leave_guest_mode() or switch vmcss).
11837 */
11838static void nested_vmx_entry_failure(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu,
11839 struct vmcs12 *vmcs12,
11840 u32 reason, unsigned long qualification)
11841{
11842 load_vmcs12_host_state(vcpu, vmcs12);
11843 vmcs12->vm_exit_reason = reason | VMX_EXIT_REASONS_FAILED_VMENTRY;
11844 vmcs12->exit_qualification = qualification;
11845 nested_vmx_succeed(vcpu);
11846 if (enable_shadow_vmcs)
11847 to_vmx(vcpu)->nested.sync_shadow_vmcs = true;
11848}
11849
11850static int vmx_check_intercept(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu,
11851 struct x86_instruction_info *info,
11852 enum x86_intercept_stage stage)
11853{
11854 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
11855}
11856
11857#ifdef CONFIG_X86_64
11858/* (a << shift) / divisor, return 1 if overflow otherwise 0 */
11859static inline int u64_shl_div_u64(u64 a, unsigned int shift,
11860 u64 divisor, u64 *result)
11861{
11862 u64 low = a << shift, high = a >> (64 - shift);
11863
11864 /* To avoid the overflow on divq */
11865 if (high >= divisor)
11866 return 1;
11867
11868 /* Low hold the result, high hold rem which is discarded */
11869 asm("divq %2\n\t" : "=a" (low), "=d" (high) :
11870 "rm" (divisor), "0" (low), "1" (high));
11871 *result = low;
11872
11873 return 0;
11874}
11875
11876static int vmx_set_hv_timer(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu, u64 guest_deadline_tsc)
11877{
11878 struct vcpu_vmx *vmx = to_vmx(vcpu);
11879 u64 tscl = rdtsc();
11880 u64 guest_tscl = kvm_read_l1_tsc(vcpu, tscl);
11881 u64 delta_tsc = max(guest_deadline_tsc, guest_tscl) - guest_tscl;
11882
11883 /* Convert to host delta tsc if tsc scaling is enabled */
11884 if (vcpu->arch.tsc_scaling_ratio != kvm_default_tsc_scaling_ratio &&
11885 u64_shl_div_u64(delta_tsc,
11886 kvm_tsc_scaling_ratio_frac_bits,
11887 vcpu->arch.tsc_scaling_ratio,
11888 &delta_tsc))
11889 return -ERANGE;
11890
11891 /*
11892 * If the delta tsc can't fit in the 32 bit after the multi shift,
11893 * we can't use the preemption timer.
11894 * It's possible that it fits on later vmentries, but checking
11895 * on every vmentry is costly so we just use an hrtimer.
11896 */
11897 if (delta_tsc >> (cpu_preemption_timer_multi + 32))
11898 return -ERANGE;
11899
11900 vmx->hv_deadline_tsc = tscl + delta_tsc;
11901 vmcs_set_bits(PIN_BASED_VM_EXEC_CONTROL,
11902 PIN_BASED_VMX_PREEMPTION_TIMER);
11903
11904 return delta_tsc == 0;
11905}
11906
11907static void vmx_cancel_hv_timer(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu)
11908{
11909 struct vcpu_vmx *vmx = to_vmx(vcpu);
11910 vmx->hv_deadline_tsc = -1;
11911 vmcs_clear_bits(PIN_BASED_VM_EXEC_CONTROL,
11912 PIN_BASED_VMX_PREEMPTION_TIMER);
11913}
11914#endif
11915

11917{
11918 if (ple_gap)
11919 shrink_ple_window(vcpu);
11920}

11939
11940static int vmx_write_pml_buffer(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu)
11941{
11942 struct vmcs12 *vmcs12;
11943 struct vcpu_vmx *vmx = to_vmx(vcpu);
11944 gpa_t gpa;
11945 struct page *page = NULL;
11946 u64 *pml_address;
11947
11948 if (is_guest_mode(vcpu)) {
11949 WARN_ON_ONCE(vmx->nested.pml_full);
11950
11951 /*
11952 * Check if PML is enabled for the nested guest.
11953 * Whether eptp bit 6 is set is already checked
11954 * as part of A/D emulation.
11955 */
11956 vmcs12 = get_vmcs12(vcpu);
11957 if (!nested_cpu_has_pml(vmcs12))
11958 return 0;
11959
11960 if (vmcs12->guest_pml_index >= PML_ENTITY_NUM) {
11961 vmx->nested.pml_full = true;
11962 return 1;
11963 }
11964
11965 gpa = vmcs_read64(GUEST_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS) & ~0xFFFull;
11966
11967 page = kvm_vcpu_gpa_to_page(vcpu, vmcs12->pml_address);
11968 if (is_error_page(page))
11969 return 0;
11970
11971 pml_address = kmap(page);
11972 pml_address[vmcs12->guest_pml_index--] = gpa;
11973 kunmap(page);
11974 kvm_release_page_clean(page);
11975 }
11976
11977 return 0;
11978}
11979
11980static void vmx_enable_log_dirty_pt_masked(struct kvm *kvm,
11981 struct kvm_memory_slot *memslot,
11982 gfn_t offset, unsigned long mask)
11983{
11984 kvm_mmu_clear_dirty_pt_masked(kvm, memslot, offset, mask);
11985}
11986
11987static void __pi_post_block(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu)
11988{
11989 struct pi_desc *pi_desc = vcpu_to_pi_desc(vcpu);
11990 struct pi_desc old, new;
11991 unsigned int dest;
11992
11993 do {
11994 old.control = new.control = pi_desc->control;
11995 WARN(old.nv != POSTED_INTR_WAKEUP_VECTOR,
11996 "Wakeup handler not enabled while the VCPU is blocked\n");
11997
11998 dest = cpu_physical_id(vcpu->cpu);
11999
12000 if (x2apic_enabled())
12001 new.ndst = dest;
12002 else
12003 new.ndst = (dest << 8) & 0xFF00;
12004
12005 /* set 'NV' to 'notification vector' */
12006 new.nv = POSTED_INTR_VECTOR;
12007 } while (cmpxchg64(&pi_desc->control, old.control,
12008 new.control) != old.control);
12009
12010 if (!WARN_ON_ONCE(vcpu->pre_pcpu == -1)) {
12011 spin_lock(&per_cpu(blocked_vcpu_on_cpu_lock, vcpu->pre_pcpu));
12012 list_del(&vcpu->blocked_vcpu_list);
12013 spin_unlock(&per_cpu(blocked_vcpu_on_cpu_lock, vcpu->pre_pcpu));
12014 vcpu->pre_pcpu = -1;
12015 }
12016}
12017
12018/*
12019 * This routine does the following things for vCPU which is going
12020 * to be blocked if VT-d PI is enabled.
12021 * - Store the vCPU to the wakeup list, so when interrupts happen
12022 * we can find the right vCPU to wake up.
12023 * - Change the Posted-interrupt descriptor as below:
12024 * 'NDST' <-- vcpu->pre_pcpu
12025 * 'NV' <-- POSTED_INTR_WAKEUP_VECTOR
12026 * - If 'ON' is set during this process, which means at least one
12027 * interrupt is posted for this vCPU, we cannot block it, in
12028 * this case, return 1, otherwise, return 0.
12029 *
12030 */
12031static int pi_pre_block(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu)
12032{
12033 unsigned int dest;
12034 struct pi_desc old, new;
12035 struct pi_desc *pi_desc = vcpu_to_pi_desc(vcpu);
12036
12037 if (!kvm_arch_has_assigned_device(vcpu->kvm) ||
12038 !irq_remapping_cap(IRQ_POSTING_CAP) ||
12039 !kvm_vcpu_apicv_active(vcpu))
12040 return 0;
12041
12042 WARN_ON(irqs_disabled());
12043 local_irq_disable();
12044 if (!WARN_ON_ONCE(vcpu->pre_pcpu != -1)) {
12045 vcpu->pre_pcpu = vcpu->cpu;
12046 spin_lock(&per_cpu(blocked_vcpu_on_cpu_lock, vcpu->pre_pcpu));
12047 list_add_tail(&vcpu->blocked_vcpu_list,
12048 &per_cpu(blocked_vcpu_on_cpu,
12049 vcpu->pre_pcpu));
12050 spin_unlock(&per_cpu(blocked_vcpu_on_cpu_lock, vcpu->pre_pcpu));
12051 }
12052
12053 do {
12054 old.control = new.control = pi_desc->control;
12055
12056 WARN((pi_desc->sn == 1),
12057 "Warning: SN field of posted-interrupts "
12058 "is set before blocking\n");
12059
12060 /*
12061 * Since vCPU can be preempted during this process,
12062 * vcpu->cpu could be different with pre_pcpu, we
12063 * need to set pre_pcpu as the destination of wakeup
12064 * notification event, then we can find the right vCPU
12065 * to wakeup in wakeup handler if interrupts happen
12066 * when the vCPU is in blocked state.
12067 */
12068 dest = cpu_physical_id(vcpu->pre_pcpu);
12069
12070 if (x2apic_enabled())
12071 new.ndst = dest;
12072 else
12073 new.ndst = (dest << 8) & 0xFF00;
12074
12075 /* set 'NV' to 'wakeup vector' */
12076 new.nv = POSTED_INTR_WAKEUP_VECTOR;
12077 } while (cmpxchg64(&pi_desc->control, old.control,
12078 new.control) != old.control);
12079
12080 /* We should not block the vCPU if an interrupt is posted for it. */
12081 if (pi_test_on(pi_desc) == 1)
12082 __pi_post_block(vcpu);
12083
12084 local_irq_enable();
12085 return (vcpu->pre_pcpu == -1);
12086}
12087
12088static int vmx_pre_block(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu)
12089{
12090 if (pi_pre_block(vcpu))
12091 return 1;
12092
12093 if (kvm_lapic_hv_timer_in_use(vcpu))
12094 kvm_lapic_switch_to_sw_timer(vcpu);
12095
12096 return 0;
12097}
12098
12099static void pi_post_block(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu)
12100{
12101 if (vcpu->pre_pcpu == -1)
12102 return;
12103
12104 WARN_ON(irqs_disabled());
12105 local_irq_disable();
12106 __pi_post_block(vcpu);
12107 local_irq_enable();
12108}
12109
12110static void vmx_post_block(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu)
12111{
12112 if (kvm_x86_ops->set_hv_timer)
12113 kvm_lapic_switch_to_hv_timer(vcpu);
12114
12115 pi_post_block(vcpu);
12116}
12117
12118/*
12119 * vmx_update_pi_irte - set IRTE for Posted-Interrupts
12120 *
12121 * @kvm: kvm
12122 * @host_irq: host irq of the interrupt
12123 * @guest_irq: gsi of the interrupt
12124 * @set: set or unset PI
12125 * returns 0 on success, < 0 on failure
12126 */
12127static int vmx_update_pi_irte(struct kvm *kvm, unsigned int host_irq,
12128 uint32_t guest_irq, bool set)
12129{
12130 struct kvm_kernel_irq_routing_entry *e;
12131 struct kvm_irq_routing_table *irq_rt;
12132 struct kvm_lapic_irq irq;
12133 struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu;
12134 struct vcpu_data vcpu_info;
12135 int idx, ret = 0;
12136
12137 if (!kvm_arch_has_assigned_device(kvm) ||
12138 !irq_remapping_cap(IRQ_POSTING_CAP) ||
12139 !kvm_vcpu_apicv_active(kvm->vcpus[0]))
12140 return 0;
12141
12142 idx = srcu_read_lock(&kvm->irq_srcu);
12143 irq_rt = srcu_dereference(kvm->irq_routing, &kvm->irq_srcu);
12144 if (guest_irq >= irq_rt->nr_rt_entries ||
12145 hlist_empty(&irq_rt->map[guest_irq])) {
12146 pr_warn_once("no route for guest_irq %u/%u (broken user space?)\n",
12147 guest_irq, irq_rt->nr_rt_entries);
12148 goto out;
12149 }
12150
12151 hlist_for_each_entry(e, &irq_rt->map[guest_irq], link) {
12152 if (e->type != KVM_IRQ_ROUTING_MSI)
12153 continue;
12154 /*
12155 * VT-d PI cannot support posting multicast/broadcast
12156 * interrupts to a vCPU, we still use interrupt remapping
12157 * for these kind of interrupts.
12158 *
12159 * For lowest-priority interrupts, we only support
12160 * those with single CPU as the destination, e.g. user
12161 * configures the interrupts via /proc/irq or uses
12162 * irqbalance to make the interrupts single-CPU.
12163 *
12164 * We will support full lowest-priority interrupt later.
12165 */
12166
12167 kvm_set_msi_irq(kvm, e, &irq);
12168 if (!kvm_intr_is_single_vcpu(kvm, &irq, &vcpu)) {
12169 /*
12170 * Make sure the IRTE is in remapped mode if
12171 * we don't handle it in posted mode.
12172 */
12173 ret = irq_set_vcpu_affinity(host_irq, NULL);
12174 if (ret < 0) {
12175 printk(KERN_INFO
12176 "failed to back to remapped mode, irq: %u\n",
12177 host_irq);
12178 goto out;
12179 }
12180
12181 continue;
12182 }
12183
12184 vcpu_info.pi_desc_addr = __pa(vcpu_to_pi_desc(vcpu));
12185 vcpu_info.vector = irq.vector;
12186
12187 trace_kvm_pi_irte_update(host_irq, vcpu->vcpu_id, e->gsi,
12188 vcpu_info.vector, vcpu_info.pi_desc_addr, set);
12189
12190 if (set)
12191 ret = irq_set_vcpu_affinity(host_irq, &vcpu_info);
12192 else
12193 ret = irq_set_vcpu_affinity(host_irq, NULL);
12194
12195 if (ret < 0) {
12196 printk(KERN_INFO "%s: failed to update PI IRTE\n",
12197 __func__);
12198 goto out;
12199 }
12200 }
12201
12202 ret = 0;
12203out:
12204 srcu_read_unlock(&kvm->irq_srcu, idx);
12205 return ret;
12206}
12207
12208static void vmx_setup_mce(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu)
12209{
12210 if (vcpu->arch.mcg_cap & MCG_LMCE_P)
12211 to_vmx(vcpu)->msr_ia32_feature_control_valid_bits |=
12212 FEATURE_CONTROL_LMCE;
12213 else
12214 to_vmx(vcpu)->msr_ia32_feature_control_valid_bits &=
12215 ~FEATURE_CONTROL_LMCE;
12216}

12326 .flush_log_dirty = vmx_flush_log_dirty,
12327 .enable_log_dirty_pt_masked = vmx_enable_log_dirty_pt_masked,
12328 .write_log_dirty = vmx_write_pml_buffer,
12329
12330 .pre_block = vmx_pre_block,
12331 .post_block = vmx_post_block,
12332
12333 .pmu_ops = &intel_pmu_ops,
12334
12335 .update_pi_irte = vmx_update_pi_irte,
12336
12337#ifdef CONFIG_X86_64
12338 .set_hv_timer = vmx_set_hv_timer,
12339 .cancel_hv_timer = vmx_cancel_hv_timer,
12340#endif
12341
12342 .setup_mce = vmx_setup_mce,
12343};
12344
12345static int __init vmx_init(void)
12346{
12347 int r = kvm_init(&vmx_x86_ops, sizeof(struct vcpu_vmx),
12348 __alignof__(struct vcpu_vmx), THIS_MODULE);
12349 if (r)
12350 return r;
12351
12352#ifdef CONFIG_KEXEC_CORE
12353 rcu_assign_pointer(crash_vmclear_loaded_vmcss,
12354 crash_vmclear_local_loaded_vmcss);
12355#endif
12356
12357 return 0;
12358}
12359
12360static void __exit vmx_exit(void)
12361{
12362#ifdef CONFIG_KEXEC_CORE
12363 RCU_INIT_POINTER(crash_vmclear_loaded_vmcss, NULL);
12364 synchronize_rcu();
12365#endif
12366
12367 kvm_exit();
12368}
